article.description: — Marcus Shaver Jr. scored 28 points and Boise State defeated Nevada 85-70 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Shaver, Akot lead Boise State past Nevada 85-70
article.linkText: Shaver, Akot lead Boise State past Nevada 85-70
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- — Marcus Shaver Jr. scored 28 points and Boise State defeated Nevada 85-70 on Wednesday night. Emmanuel Akot added 23 points for the Broncos (11-4, 2-0 Mountain West Conference. Shaver and Akot both went 4 of 8 from 3-point range. Naje Smith added 11 points. Grant Sherfield scored 26 points for Nevada (7-6, 1-1). Desmond Cambridge scored 14 points. Warren Washington added 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25
